FBIS3-10267 "drlat043_c_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 MEXICO Canadian Foreign Minister Begins Visit End To U.S. Embargo of Cuba Urged LD0203151594 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 1430 GMT 2 Mar 94 LD0203151594 Montreal Radio Canada International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Canada and Mexico have agreed to work together to push for an end to the U.S.-imposed trade embargo against Cuba. Canada's foreign minister, Andre Ouellet, and his Mexican counterpart, Manuel Tello, met in Mexico City yesterday, and they said it is time to convince the U.S. to end the isolation of Cuba. Neither Canada nor Mexico observe the U.S.-led embargo. The embargo has been in force since the 1960's.
